# Streamlit App Walkthrough

## Summary
I created a Streamlit application [app.py](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/AirPlay/app.py) for MediaPipe Hand Landmark detection. The app supports both image upload and live video inference.

## Verification Results
### Installation
`streamlit` and its dependencies (including `pandas`, `altair`, etc.) were successfully installed in the virtual environment.

### App Validation
- [app.py](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/AirPlay/app.py) was created with the necessary imports and logic.
- `python -m py_compile app.py` passed, confirming no syntax errors.

## How to Run
To start the app, run the following command in your terminal:

```bash
./.venv/bin/streamlit run app.py
```

This will open the app in your browser where you can switch between "Upload Image" and "Live Video" modes.
